{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5c79c640-09a9-4a13-bd82-de9f3ceec24e","content":"**Yes, you will hit a compatibility issue.** MSTest v4 **dropped support for `net6.0` and `net7.0`** — it only supports:\n\n- **`net8.0`+** (for .NET)\n- **`net462`+** (for .NET Framework)\n\nYour project targets `net6.0`, so upgrading MSTest packages to 4.x will fail to restore or produce build errors.\n\n### What to do\n\n1. **Retarget to `net8.0`** (or later) in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n   ```\n2. **Then** upgrade MSTest to v4.\n\nNote that `net6.0` is already out of support (EOL November 2024), so retargeting to `net8.0` is recommended regardless.\n\nWould you like me to retarget and upgrade for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"203a7bf1-ddd6-42ed-b159-6f5792cb53b6","outputTokens":223},"id":"8c35cf64-bc88-4676-94d4-59cac6e629ec","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:01:08.726Z","parentId":"bfffdd99-7ac0-408d-9794-4d15922723c3"}
